   <head>An Epigram on the same Occasion.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">little giv'n at Chapel Door! —</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">This People doubtless must be poor:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So much at Gaming thrown away! —</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No Nation sure so rich as they.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, 'twere greatly for your Glory,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Should those, who shall transmit your Story,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Their Notions of your Grandeur frame,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Not as you , but as you</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
